node.text:
Time to reflect on the report prepared by the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change's latest findings, approved by 195 member states on Friday, which deals with the physical science basis of climate change and outlines how humans are altering the planet in ways that are becoming irreversible.
This report is a RALLYING CRY for us ALL to act like our house is on fire because it is! The most hardcore  climate change denier can not ignore the historical wildfires and ensuing mud slides, torrential rains,  and floods, that sweep homes cars and people away. 
Our new normal now includes epic wildfires, super storms,  off the chart hurricanes, bomb cyclones, floods, shoreline erosion, mass human migration due to islands sinking into the sea, and inlets with toxic algae blooms!  Our life sustaining coral reefs are crumbling as oceans heat up, and the Gulf Stream which controls our weather and water temperatures is headed for  catastrophic eminent collapse! 
Drought, insect proliferation, disease and epidemics dominate the news and our lives. They were all predicted and ignored in the first report prepared by the US Dept of Defense! They did the study because they knew dwindling resources can lead to wars over food and water. 
My friends we must respond to this with the urgency and attention we owe future generations STARTING NOW! The biggest thing we can do is DEMAND that our representatives react to this report with Wide sweeping changes ..adopting clean green alternative energy and break our dependence on fossil fuels! 
Let’s keep sharing ways we can make a difference in our daily lives and let’s VOTE IN REPRESENTATIVES that make THIS A PRIORITY! We can do it together because we must!💙🌎💚♻️ #climatechange #climateaction #coderedforhumanity 
🌟remember a #healthylifestyle requires a #healthy #planet and our planet needs intensive care urgently ! 🚩

The Hamptons pride trail is brought to you in partnership with the African Community and Conservation Foundation (ACCF).
This celebration of lions and the people who live alongside them will launch on World Lion Day, 10th August 2021. Life-size lion sculptures, designed and made by some of the planet’s foremost artists, like @donnakaranthewoman  who helped organize #thehamptons artistic community. These lions that will roam the streets to highlight the threats currently faced by ‘the King of Beasts’, and to raise vital funds to support community conservation and livelihoods impacted by Covid-19 across Africa. 
#tuskliontrial #thelionsarecoming
